channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Israel vows to eliminate Hamas in Rafah
item.description: Israel's defense minister said its military operation in Rafah will continue until Hamas is eliminated from the southern city and "the entire Gaza Strip," or until the first hostage returns. Follow for live updates.

item.title: May 7, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Israeli airstrikes killed multiple people in Rafah early Tuesday, Palestinian officials said,

item.title: Body of 6th construction worker killed in Baltimore Key Bridge collapse recovered
item.description: The body of the sixth victim killed in the Baltimore Francis Scott Key Bridge collapse has been recovered, authorities said Tuesday.

item.title: Stormy Daniels testifies in Trump's hush money trial
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's hush money trial continued Tuesday in New York.

item.title: Man trying to spread HIV through sex with men and teenage boys sentenced to 30 years
item.description: A 34-year-old Idaho man has been imprisoned for at least 30 years after "purposely" trying to spread HIV through sexual contact with both men and teenage boys.

item.title: Deadly tornado reported in Oklahoma after barrage of destructive storms
item.description: Destructive storms and tornadoes hit the Central US on Monday and Tuesday, including at least one deadly tornado.

item.title: Michigan Governor declares state of emergency in parts of state over tornadoes
item.description: Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer has declared a state of emergency in areas of Michigan due to the tornadoes that hit the area Tuesday.

item.title: May 6, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Israeli airstrikes killed multiple people in Rafah early Tuesday, Palestinian officials said.

item.title: Trump's classified documents trial delayed indefinitely
item.description: The judge overseeing former President Trump's classified documents case has now indefinitely postponed the trial pending resolution of outstanding pretrial litigation.
